# URMA — User Risk Monitoring Agent
 
Detects fake accounts, bots, and suspicious activity on a job application platform using AI.
 
## What it does
Analyzes user behavior data and uses Gemini to assign a risk score, level, and flag reason to each user. High-risk users automatically trigger alerts.
 
## Backend — FastAPI + NeonDB + Gemini
Three endpoints:
- `GET /users` — returns all users sorted by risk score
- `POST /scan` — runs Gemini analysis on all users and writes results back to DB
- `GET /alerts` — returns all unresolved alerts
 
## Frontend — React
- Metric cards showing total, high, medium, and clean user status
- User table with risk scores, levels, signals, and flag reasons
- Alerts panel showing auto-generated high-risk alerts
- "Run AI scan" button triggers the backend scan of database and refreshes the dashboard